Skoda Auto Expects Car Sales to Rise 10% in 2011, CTK Reports

-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 
2011-09-13T12:47:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-13/skoda-auto-expects-car-sales-to-rise-10-in-2011-ctk-reports.html
Skoda Auto AS plans to sell at
least 840,000 vehicles this year, up from 762,000 cars in 2010,
 CTK  reported, citing a forecast from Chief Executive Officer
Winfried Vahland.  The carmaker expects double-digit 2011 sales growth that
should “significantly” exceed 800,000 units, CTK cited Vahland
as saying.  Skoda plans to start producing a new model in its Mlada
Boleslav,  Czech Republic , plant next year. The daily production
capacity at the plant should also be boosted to 1,200 Octavia
models from the current 800 units, CTK added.  To contact the reporter on this story: Lenka Ponikelska in
Prague   lponikelska1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  